# Next (inlined at build time — non-sensitive only, this ends up in the client bundle)
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=   # e.g. https://models.rahmanef.com — public origin, used as the pre-hydration SSR fallback before window.location is available. NOT a secret.

# Set on the HOST running `next build`/`next start` (Dokploy app env, .env.local, etc — server-only, not inlined into the client bundle):
#   SITE_URL         same value as NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL above — public origin, used server-side to resolve behind a reverse proxy (see lib/origin.ts)

# Set on the Convex deployment (npx convex env set ...):
#   MODELS_ENC_KEY   base64 of 32 bytes  ->  openssl rand -base64 32   (encrypts BYOK keys at rest)
#   SITE_URL         same value again — used to build the OpenRouter OAuth callback URL and the MCP server's self-reported name
#   JWT_PRIVATE_KEY + JWKS  ->  npx @convex-dev/auth   (Convex Cloud does all of this)
